<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="106" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,925,1598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1429,1454]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[323,459,1429,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis box="[323,459,1429,1454]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">H. aberrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single male from 
<collectingCountry box="[915,997,1429,1454]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(examined). It is recorded here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[320,381,1465,1490]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">India</collectingCountry>
. The specimens from Lunglei differ from the 
<typeStatus box="[889,937,1466,1490]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
in having the male plate gradually narrowed and the basal processes of the aedeagal shaft serrated mesally and not visible in lateral aspect; however, these differences are probably geographical variations. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1140,1537,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisetosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[967,1140,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">H. longisetosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1147,1236,1537,1562]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1147,1236,1537,1562]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1290,1395,1537,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thapai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1290,1395,1537,1562]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">H. thapai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="5" pageNumber="106" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and can be differentiated based on the characters given in the key.
</paragraph>
